mi edu for more information or to reserve a vehicle  In order to drive an Infirmary vehicle  a cadet must become an Institute Driver  To do so   read the following General Order  print and complete the attached form  and bring it along with current driver s license to the Post Police or Infirmary  The process of approval to become an Institute Drive may take a couple of days  Cadets should also complete Transportation Waiver and bring completed form to the Infirmary  General Order 23   VMI Driver Qualification and Vehicle Use Policy Institute Driver Form   Attachment A General Order 23 Transportation Waiver VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 